{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce mandatory registration of white goods to improve product recalls",
        "additional_details": "Without a functioning recall system, potentially dangerous appliances cannot easily be traced. The lack of registration of white goods contributes to an average failure rate of 80-90% for recalls. Many people are unaware of the registration process and have never proactively checked if their white goods were subject to a recall. \r\n\r\nThe registration changes proposed would be simple for consumers and could be incorporated into existing transactions.",
        "background": "An estimated 60 fires a week are caused by faulty white goods. To improve product recalls Government should mandate the registration of high-risk white goods at: \r\n\r\n\u2022 The point of purchase \r\n\u2022 When a property is sold \r\n\u2022 During home insurance applications",
